Tokyo Stock Prices Close Lower
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   TOKYO (AP) -- The Nikkei shed 16.54 points to close at 16,228.90. 
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Mariners 5, White Sox 4
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   SEATTLE (AP) -- Edgar Martinez drove in a pair of runs to increase his major
league-leading total to 57 and John Halama won his sixth straight decision as
the Seattle Mariners rallied past the Chicago White Sox 5-4 Monday. Martinez,
who has hit in 14 consecutive games, went 2-for-2 with a pair of singles and two
walks.
</P>
