<HEADLINE> PM-NY--Missing Canoeist, 1st-Ld writethru, 114  </HEADLINE>
Authorities find missing canoeist in Delaware County
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANDES, N.Y. (AP) -- The body of a 39-year-old Pennsylvania man
has been recovered from a Delaware County lake, according to New
York state police.
</P>
<P>
   Vernon Ragsdale, 39, of Philadelphia was canoeing in Perch Lake
after 6:30 p.m. Sunday when he fell out of the boat, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Troopers say Ragsdale was apparently not wearing a life jacket
and could not swim. Two workers at the campground saw Ragsdale
struggling and slip from the edge of the boat before they could
reach him.
</P>
<P>
   Rescue operations ran until 11:45 p.m. Saturday and resumed
again on Sunday before they found Ragsdale's body, about 120 feet
from the shore.
</P>
<P>
   Andes is 61 miles south of Albany.
</P>
