<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Withdrawal Encourages U.S.  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP)-- The United States is encouraged by Ethiopian
withdrawals which reportedly have begun in the western areas of
Eritrea, the State Department said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Spokesman Philip Reeker called on the Ethiopian government to
desist from all further offensive actions, including air attacks of
the kind carried out against a power plant near Massawa and against
the Asmara airport.
</P>
<P>
   Reeker said the United States wants to avoid any interruption in
the flow of humanitarian supplies to the civilian victims of the
conflict.
</P>
<P>
   He added that U.S. officials have received confirmation from
Eritrea that it has left all territories its forces forcibly
occupied since May 6, 1998.
</P>
