<HEADLINE> Pie Hurled at Agriculture Secretary  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Agriculture Secretary Dan Glickman wanted to
make a point about nutrition. An animal rights vigilante wanted to
make a point about meat.
</P>
<P>
   The two met Tuesday in a cream-pie collision.
</P>
<P>
   People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals said one of its
members, Arathi Jayaram of Mansfield, Ohio, ran onto the stage at a
government nutrition summit and heaved a tofu cream pie, yelling:
''Shame on you, Dan Glickman, for pushing meat and promoting animal
cruelty.''
</P>
<P>
   PETA's beef with Glickman, said spokeswoman Dawn Carr, is that
he won't ''acknowledge that a meat-based diet is killing people.''
</P>
<P>
   Glickman took the public smear with good humor and a bad feel
for filling, telling reporters he thought it had been an apple pie.
</P>
<P>
   Carr said Jayaram was taken into police custody.
</P>
</TEXT>
