<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded
heavily Tuesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
Advanced Micro Devices, up $11 at $85
Micron Technology Inc., up $3.50 at $68.125
</P>
<P>
   Lehman Brothers analyst Dan Niles, who recently joined the firm
from BancBoston Robertson Stephens, began coverage AMD with an
''outperform'' rating and Micron with a ''buy'' rating.
</P>
<P>
Telefonica SA, up $5.50 at $62.875
Alcatel SA, up $5.938 at $54.938
</P>
<P>
   Shares rose after France Telecom agreed to buy Britain's Orange
from Vodafone Air Touch PLC for about $37.6 billion in cash and
stock. The deal raised expectations that other European
telecommunications companies will combine.
</P>
