Office Depot Inc., down $0.50 at $7
</P>
<P>
   Shares fell for a second straight session after the company said
poor technology-product sales and a strong dollar will cause it to
miss earnings expectations for the second quarter. Today, Merrill
Lynch and Goldman Sachs cut their ratings on Office Depot.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
Wesley Jessen VisionCare Inc., up $3.688 at $36.875
</P>
<P>
   Swiss pharmaceutical giant Novartis' eye care unit, CIBA Vision,
has agreed to buy contact lens maker Wesley Jessen for about $785
million. The deal tops a hostile bid valued at about $725 million
that Bausch &AMP; Lomb Inc. made earlier this month for Wesley Jessen.
</P>
