SDL Inc., up $24.125 at $221.875
</P>
<P>
   JDS Uniphase Corp. extended SDL's contract to supply pump lasers
through 2001. SDL said the extended contract more than doubles the
base quantities of the original contract. Investment bank Thomas
Weisel Partners raised its rating to ''strong buy'' from ''buy.''
</P>
<P>
Splash Technology Holdings Inc., down $3.375 at $7.875
</P>
<P>
   US Bancorp Piper Jaffray analyst C. Eugene Munster cut his
rating and his price target for the company, a maker of color
servers. Munster said revenue from a new color printer server
product line won't be realized until the fourth quarter.
</P>
