<HEADLINE> Mariners Put Meche on 15-Day DL  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE (AP) -- Right-hander Gil Meche, who developed a ''dead
arm'' in his last start, was placed on the 15-day disabled list by
the Seattle Mariners on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Meche, 21, was disabled retroactive to Monday and the Mariners
recalled right-hander Kevin Hodges from Triple-A Tacoma to take
Meche's roster spot.
</P>
<P>
   Meche underwent tests, but doctors could determine only that
Meche's right shoulder had been strained.
</P>
<P>
   ''The only thing that's come out of it is a dead arm,'' Meche
said. ''My arm is just tired. It's not a big concern for me because
it doesn't hurt. Hopefully, everything goes well in the next couple
of days.''
</P>
<P>
   Meche, who felt the injury Sunday in Tampa Bay, is supposed to
pitch a simulated game on Friday.
</P>
<P>
   ''We want to treat this with caution,'' manager Lou Piniella
said. ''Gil's got a great career ahead of him and we don't want to
do anything to jeopardize it.''
</P>
<P>
   Meche was 1-4 with a 4.21 ERA in 10 starts and 57 2-3 innings
this season. He was bothered by tightness in his right shoulder in
spring training.
</P>
<P>
   The Mariners already have two starting pitchers, left-hander
Jamie Moyer and right-hander Freddy Garcia, on the disabled list.
Moyer is scheduled to come off the disabled list and pitch Friday
night against San Diego.
</P>
</TEXT>
