<HEADLINE> Kasparov Wins Sarajevo Chess Title  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SARAJEVO, Bosnia-Herzegovina (AP) -- World chess champion Garry
Kasparov often visited Sarajevo during its 3{-year siege and played
against Sarajevans while shells and bullets were raining on the
city.
</P>
<P>
   On Monday, he won his second chess title in Sarajevo in two
years, defeating a dozen of the world's best players in the Bosnia
2000 tournament.
</P>
<P>
   The 37-year-old Russian received frantic applause from
spectators for his victory and for his support for the city during
the war.
</P>
<P>
   The Bosnia 2000 tournament, which lasted almost two weeks, was
organized to mark the eighth year of Bosnia's membership in the
United Nations.
</P>
