<HEADLINE> Tigers 7, Rangers 4  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DETROIT (AP) -- Dean Palmer homered and drove in five runs, and
Brian Moehler won for the first time since April 11 as the Detroit
Tigers beat the Texas Rangers 7-4 on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   The Tigers won for just the second time in their last six games.
Detroit once again played without former Rangers star Juan
Gonzalez, who missed his second straight game with a strained left
foot.
</P>
<P>
   Texas is 3-5 on a nine-game road trip that ends Thursday and has
lost five of seven since a seven-game winning streak.
</P>
<P>
   Palmer hit a three-run homer in the third. He also had a
sacrifice fly in the first and an RBI single in the seventh. His
homer was the Tigers' first with two on since Palmer did it April
17 against Tampa Bay.
</P>
<P>
   Moehler (2-3) gave up three runs and seven hits in 5 2-3
innings. He was making his third start since coming off the
disabled list from an emergency appendectomy April 22.
</P>
<P>
   The Tigers hadn't scored any runs for Moehler in the other two
starts but jumped on Esteban Loaiza (3-3) for five runs after three
innings.
</P>
<P>
   Loaiza, who had his last two starts, allowed five runs and 10
hits in five-plus innings.
</P>
<P>
   Danny Patterson, sent to Detroit in the nine-player deal that
included Gonzalez, pitched 2 2-3 innings and left after allowing an
RBI single to Chad Curtis in the ninth. Todd Jones got the final
out for his 14th save in 15 chances.
</P>
<P>
   Three straight hits, including Bobby Higginson's RBI single, and
a sacrifice fly from Palmer gave the Tigers a 2-0 lead in the
first.
</P>
<P>
   Palmer's 10th home run was one of five straight hits that made
it 5-0 in the third. Detroit didn't score more only because Rich
Becker, who started the inning with a single, was picked off first
by catcher Ivan Rodriguez.
</P>
<P>
   Moehler was cruising with a three-hitter and had faced just one
batter over the minimum through five innings before the Rangers
knocked him out with a three-run sixth. Luis Alicea hit a two-run
double after a leadoff double from Mike Lamb and Royce Clayton's
single, and Rodriguez added a sacrifice fly.
</P>
<P>
   Palmer had an RBI single and Robert Fick a sacrifice fly as the
Tigers added two more in the seventh.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Tigers INF Gregg Jefferies is expected to miss at least a
month with a severe left hamstring pull he suffered legging out an
infield hit Monday. He went on the DL Tuesday and was replaced on
the 25-man roster by C Javier Cardona, who was recalled from
Triple-A Toledo. ... RHP Francisco Cordero was the first of the
nine players involved in the Tigers-Rangers trade to appear in the
series when he relieved Loaiza in the sixth. ... Palmer's
club-leading 10th homer leaves Minnesota as the only major league
team without a double-digit home run hitter. ... Moehler's only
other win this season was a 5-2 decision over Seattle in Comerica
Park's inaugural game.
</P>
</TEXT>
